Midgaard has attempted at various points to bring psionicist academic institutions under the Registry's oversight, and at various points has failed. The current arrangement involves a voluntary notification protocol — practitioners who perform cognitive assessment or intervention in civic contexts are expected to file a notification rather than a license — which the Continuity faction treats as satisfactory and the Reckoning faction treats as inadequate. The Wizard's Keep's Triple-Ledger Rule is the model the psionicist academies have explicitly declined to follow, on the grounds that most psionicist applications cannot be externally verified in the ways the ledger rule assumes. Midgaard's practical use of psionicists is primarily in witness credibility assessment for Registry proceedings — practitioners who can assess whether testimony reflects genuine memory versus confabulation are valuable to a city where record integrity is foundational. The Guard Command has a parallel and somewhat more covert relationship with psionicist practitioners for detainee assessment, which the Continuity faction prefers not to document formally.

