Kiess's access to Void Citadel documentation through the anti-sealed-warrant archive has made the city's scholarly community uniquely aware of the Citadel-psionicist lineage connection that other cities' research contexts allow practitioners to avoid examining. Kiess scholars who have worked with both the Citadel documentation and the Assertion Wing's technical literature have produced assessments suggesting partial derivation that the psionicist academic tradition would prefer remain in the anti-sealed-warrant archive rather than circulating in standard scholarly channels. Wall Command's use of psionicists is primarily in threat assessment and tactical planning: practitioners who can model opponent cognition — assess likely decision-making patterns, identify stress vulnerabilities — provide planning value without the political complications of direct intervention operations. Kiess's frontier context means psionicist threat-assessment work is operationally significant rather than primarily institutional.

