Rivennid experience the world as network — connective tissue, information flows, nodes of concentration and distribution. Psionicist cognitive architecture work, from a Rivennid perspective, maps directly onto network topology: memories are nodes, behavioral dispositions are flow patterns, and direct cognitive access is a form of network traversal. Rivennid psionicists in Midgaard's institutional context tend to be unusually precise in their assessment work because their native perceptual framework provides a pre-existing vocabulary for the kind of structural analysis that the Pale Ledger tradition developed through deliberate research. The Registry's cognitive assessment uses benefit most from Rivennid practitioners specifically because their network-topology framing produces assessments that can be cross-referenced against Registry documentation records — the node/flow model of memory maps onto the record/precedent model of the Registry in ways that make Rivennid practitioner reports more useful for Registry proceedings than assessments from practitioners using other conceptual frameworks.

